                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">792.94/14</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Siamese Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prince Damras</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-18">May 18,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hornbeck</hi>: You have no doubt seen articles in
                    the newspapers of the 13th and 14th May that Siam’s neighbours are alarmed by
                    the increasing influence of Japan, and that some sort of special treaty has been
                    signed with that country.</p>
                <p>Remembering that you have once asked me about the Japanese influence in my
                    country, and I then said that I had no information respecting <pb facs="0282"
                        n="170" xml:id="pg_170"/> the matter, I am now in a position to inform you
                    that there is no truth in the reports given by the Associated Press to the
                    various newspapers, and I am instructed to assure you that it is the policy of
                    His Majesty’s Government to strengthen the bonds of friendship with all the
                    treaty Powers alike, and not with any single one in particular.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Damras</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
